const faqItems = [{"question": "How do I find an accountant in Birmingham that AI tools recommend?", "answer": "Start by checking how you appear in ChatGPT, Gemini and Perplexity for queries like \"best accountants in Birmingham\" and \"accountant for small business in Birmingham\". If you are not named, the gap is usually entity clarity: inconsistent firm name, missing ICAEW or ACCA listing, no Trustpilot or Google reviews, or a website that does not state your specialisms clearly. Fix those first, then expect to see your firm surface in AI answers within a few weeks."}, {"question": "Why do AI tools like ChatGPT recommend the same handful of Birmingham accountants?", "answer": "AI systems pull from sources they trust. In Birmingham that usually means firms with strong Companies House data, professional body membership, multiple independent reviews, and content explaining their niche. The firms that get named consistently tend to publish guides, appear in regional press, and keep their digital footprint aligned across every platform."}, {"question": "What is the difference between traditional SEO and AI search optimisation for Birmingham accountants?", "answer": "Traditional SEO targets clicks from search results. AI search optimisation targets being named and cited inside AI generated answers. Many users now ask ChatGPT or Gemini directly rather than scrolling Google. If your firm is not visible inside the AI answer itself, the click never happens because no list of links is shown."}, {"question": "Do Birmingham accountants need to be FCA regulated to appear in AI search?", "answer": "Most accountancy work does not require FCA regulation, only certain investment business activities do. AI tools care more about clarity than regulation. They want to see consistent firm details, professional body membership (ICAEW, ACCA, AAT, CIMA), Companies House data and verifiable client reviews. Accuracy matters more than regulatory status."}, {"question": "How long does it take to improve AI search visibility for an accountancy firm in Birmingham?", "answer": "Most firms see early movement within four to six weeks once entity clarity work is done and ecosystem validation is in place. Full visibility, where AI tools name your firm in answers to commercial queries, typically takes three to six months depending on starting position and how active competitors are."}, {"question": "What does an AI search visibility audit cover for a Birmingham accountant?", "answer": "Our audit tests your firm across ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot and Google AI Overviews using real client queries for Birmingham. You see exactly which queries return your firm, which return competitors, and the five signal layers that need work to change that. The audit is delivered as a written report within five working days."}];
